A car on fire crashed into Glasgow Airport, causing chaos and panic.
British Prime Minister Gordon Brown confirmed it was an attack, leading to heightened security levels.
The incident was linked to foiled car bomb plots in London, indicating a new threat.
Two suspects were arrested in connection with the attacks.
Security was tightened at airports across Britain.
The public was urged to remain vigilant and support authorities.
The highest security alert level was raised, signifying an imminent attack.
The incidents in London and Glasgow were seen as linked, highlighting the need for continued vigilance.
